<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF436AFCF7EF90741439B332" pageId="184" pageNumber="946" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF436AFCF7EF90741439B332" blockId="184.[2066,2660,1506,1930]" lastBlockId="184.[1453,2661,1936,3351]" pageId="184" pageNumber="946">
Subgenus Pizonyx; 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF436AFCF6DF90741788BD7C" authorityName="Eversmann" authorityYear="1845" box="[2339,2440,1581,1614]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="184" pageNumber="946" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brandtii">brandtii</taxonomicName>
species group. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF436AFCF7E8900116D7BD47" authorityName="Kastschenko" authorityYear="1905" box="[2068,2263,1624,1653]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="184" pageNumber="946" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sibiricus">Myotis sibiricus</taxonomicName>
is traditionally considered a subspecies of M. brandi under the name M. b. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF436AFCF79790FA16C7BDF6" box="[2155,2247,1699,1732]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Murina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="184" pageNumber="946" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gracilis">gracilis</taxonomicName>
, which is now considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF436AFCF7389096175EBDDE" authorityName="Kastschenko" authorityYear="1905" box="[2244,2398,1743,1772]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="184" pageNumber="946" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sibiricus">M. sibiricus</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF436AFCF68D9096142ABDDE" box="[2417,2602,1743,1772]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="184" pageNumber="946" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gracilis">Myotis gracilis</taxonomicName>
has been variously recognized as a distinct species, but 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF436AFCF76F9147172BBC09" authorityName="Kastschenko" authorityYear="1905" box="[2195,2347,1822,1851]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="184" pageNumber="946" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sibiricus">M. sibiricus</taxonomicName>
1s the oldest available name and thus has nomenclatural priority. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF436AFCF7E8913016D9BCB8" authorityName="Kastschenko" authorityYear="1905" box="[2068,2265,1897,1930]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="184" pageNumber="946" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sibiricus">Myotis sibiricus</taxonomicName>
appears to be sister species to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF436AFCFA2991C9186ABC83" authorityName="Eversmann" authorityYear="1845" box="[1493,1642,1936,1969]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="184" pageNumber="946" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brandtii">M. brandtii</taxonomicName>
, but they are very tae Both species are very peculiarly embedded in the New World clade of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF436AFCF8D491EE197CBCEA" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[1832,1916,1975,2008]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="184" pageNumber="946" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
, although the exact position of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF436AFCF6C391EE17D3BCEA" authorityName="Eversmann" authorityYear="1845" box="[2367,2515,1975,2008]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="184" pageNumber="954" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brandtii">M. brandtii</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF436AFCF5E791EE1802B332" authorityName="Kastschenko" authorityYear="1905" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="184" pageNumber="946" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sibiricus">M. sibiricus</taxonomicName>
with respect to the New World 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF436AFCF84191861610B332" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[1981,2064,2015,2048]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="184" pageNumber="946" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
is still not completely clear. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
